body:
App renders a black screen on Vercel due to three compounding issues: JSX never compiled (missing Vite React plugin), asset URLs broken (relative base path), and client-side routes returning 404s (no rewrite rule).

## Changes

- **`vite.config.js`** — Add `@vitejs/plugin-react` (was in `devDependencies` but never wired into the config; without it Vite ships untransformed JSX and the app never mounts). Fix `base: "./"` → `base: "/"` so asset hashes resolve correctly from Vercel's CDN.

```js
// before
export default defineConfig({ base: "./" })

// after
export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [react()],
  base: "/",
})
```

- **`vercel.json`** — Add catch-all rewrite to `index.html`, mirroring the existing `netlify.toml` config, so Vercel hands all routes to the React app instead of returning 404.

```json
{ "rewrites": [{ "source": "/(.*)", "destination": "/index.html" }] }
```
